    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_133951456" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/133951456" />
    <a title="Chrissie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/632247-chrissie"><img alt="Chrissie" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1321799585p2/632247.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/133951456?book_show_action=true">Aug 11, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Chrissie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Chrissie" href="/user/show/632247-chrissie">Chrissie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/632247-chrissie?shelf=philo-psychol">philo-psychol</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/632247-chrissie?shelf=usa">usa</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/632247-chrissie?shelf=swedish-narration">swedish-narration</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/632247-chrissie?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/632247-chrissie?shelf=travel">travel</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/632247-chrissie?shelf=ww2">ww2</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/632247-chrissie?shelf=hf">hf</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/632247-chrissie?shelf=2020-read">2020-read</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/632247-chrissie?shelf=audible-uk">audible-uk</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/632247-chrissie?shelf=argentina">argentina</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer133951456" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13015628160358010420">Wow, this is powerful!<br/><br/>Austrian author Stefan Zweig (1891 – 1942) wrote <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/59151.Chess_Story' title='Chess Story by Stefan Zweig' rel='nofollow noopener'>Chess Story</a> in 1941, the year before his and his second wife’s death by suicide. He was of Jewish background. With Hitler’ rise in power he and his wife had left Austria for England, had moved on to the US and then to Brazil, where the novella was completed. It is the only one of Zweig’s books that deals directly with Nazism. <br/><br/>A steamboat travelling from New York to Buenos Aires has on board a handful of chess enthusiasts. The</span>
  <span id="freeText13015628160358010420" style="display:none">Wow, this is powerful!<br /><br />Austrian author Stefan Zweig (1891 – 1942) wrote <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/59151.Chess_Story" title="Chess Story by Stefan Zweig" rel="nofollow noopener">Chess Story</a> in 1941, the year before his and his second wife’s death by suicide. He was of Jewish background. With Hitler’ rise in power he and his wife had left Austria for England, had moved on to the US and then to Brazil, where the novella was completed. It is the only one of Zweig’s books that deals directly with Nazism. <br /><br />A steamboat travelling from New York to Buenos Aires has on board a handful of chess enthusiasts. They discover to their surprise that the world’s master chess champion is on board their ship! He proves to be haughty, arrogant and a decidedly unfriendly type, but at the cost of a large fee he agrees to a game or two. Of course, those playing against him lose. A passenger strolling by observes the game, offers some advice, and surprise, surprise a tie is reached! Who is this man who says he is no expert and has not played chess in decades? Discovering how he came to know chess and what happens on the boat is the story. <br /><br />Now, I don’t know how to play chess, and I was totally pulled in. You need not know the game to enjoy this book. The history behind the unknown player will draw you in. Tension mounts. You absolutely do not want to put the book down! It is a novella you pick up and read in one sitting.<br /><br />For years I have wanted to read this / listen to it. I discovered that there exists an audio version translated into Swedish, and it was available to me. The title in Swedish is <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/36594890.Schacknovell" title="Schacknovell by Stefan Zweig" rel="nofollow noopener">Schacknovell</a>. Hugo Hultenberg does a fantastic translation form the original German to Swedish. The text is straightforward, crystal clear, grammatically correct and, as I have pointed out, extremely engaging. The audiobook is superbly narrated by Gert Lundstedt. If you know Swedish, perhaps even if your knowledge is only rudimentary, I believe you will be able to follow the text. I highly recommend this audiobook. <br /><br />I have given both the book and the audio narration five stars. Don’t miss this gem. It has no weak part. The ending is perfect, as is the middle and the start.<br /><br />********************<br /><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/59151.Chess_Story" title="Chess Story by Stefan Zweig" rel="nofollow noopener">Chess Story</a> 5 stars<br /><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/37678644.Amok" title="Amok by Stefan Zweig" rel="nofollow noopener">Amok</a> 5 stars<br /><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/4455573.Burning_Secret" title="Burning Secret by Stefan Zweig" rel="nofollow noopener">Burning Secret</a> 4 stars<br /><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/59149.Beware_of_Pity" title="Beware of Pity by Stefan Zweig" rel="nofollow noopener">Beware of Pity</a> 3 stars<br /><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/629429.The_World_of_Yesterday" title="The World of Yesterday by Stefan Zweig" rel="nofollow noopener">The World of Yesterday</a> 3 stars<br /><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/24456813.Letter_From_An_Unknown_Woman" title="Letter From An Unknown Woman by Stefan Zweig" rel="nofollow noopener">Letter From An Unknown Woman</a> 3 stars<br /><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/28364718.Summer_Before_the_Dark_Stefan_Zweig_and_Joseph_Roth__Ostend_1936" title="Summer Before the Dark Stefan Zweig and Joseph Roth, Ostend 1936 by Volker Weidermann" rel="nofollow noopener">Summer Before the Dark: Stefan Zweig and Joseph Roth, Ostend 1936</a> 3 stars<br /><br /> <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="13015628160358010420" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


